premise_source_doc_sentence: Hyperacusis  (  or hyperacousis  )  also known as phonophobia is a debilitating hearing disorder characterized by an increased sensitivity to certain frequency and volume ranges of sound  (  a collapsed tolerance to usual environmental sound  )  .

Researchers interested in understanding the neurophysiological underpinnings of amblyaudia consider it to be a brain based hearing disorder that may be inherited or that may result from auditory deprivation during critical periods of brain development .
It is thought that cortical deafness could be a part of a spectrum of an overall cortical hearing disorder .
Individuals with amblyaudia have normal hearing sensitivity  (  in other words they hear soft sounds  )  but have difficulty hearing in noisy environments like restaurants or classrooms .
It may also be related to , caused by , or confused with `` hyperacusis '' , extreme sensitivity to loud sounds Phonophobia also refers to an extreme form of misophonia .
